  <discussion>Sphagnum steerei is usually easily recognized in the field by its dense growth habit and dark brown color.  Its ecology is somewhat unclear due to taxonomic confusion with S. imbricatum in the strict sense and S. austinii (R. E. Andrus 1987).  The latter is the only species in the imbricatum complex that occurs where S. steerei does.  Contrary to the view of H. A. Crum (1997), S. steerei is quite distinct from S. affine and S. austinii.  There is no range overlap with either of those species and the macroscopic appearance is also quite different.</discussion>
